# Cache strategy: split the browser TTL from the Cloudflare edge TTL.
#
# The old rule (max-age=0, s-maxage=86400, must-revalidate) forced every RETURN
# visit to spend a full network round trip on a 304 revalidation. Measured from
# Taiwan that is ~80ms wasted per return visit. This is the one change that
# actually moves the needle (first-visit TTFB is bound by handshake + edge
# distance, not by these headers).
#
# - Cache-Control (what the browser sees): short max-age so a fresh publish shows
#   up quickly, plus stale-while-revalidate so a slightly-stale return visit is
#   served instantly from cache while the browser refreshes in the background.
#   Do NOT add s-maxage / must-revalidate / no-cache here: Cloudflare disables
#   stale-while-revalidate when any of those are present and returns EXPIRED.
# - Cloudflare-CDN-Cache-Control (edge only, stripped before it reaches the
#   browser): a longer edge TTL so the HTML stays a cache HIT at the POP.
#
# A new deployment purges the edge cache automatically. Requires the zone's
# Edge TTL Cache Rule set to "Respect Origin" (not "Override origin") - an
# override rule ignores these headers entirely and was the root cause of a
# prior incident where the edge served day-old HTML referencing bundle hashes
# an atomic deploy had already deleted, blanking /interactive.
/
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, stale-while-revalidate=86400, stale-if-error=604800
  Cloudflare-CDN-Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400, stale-while-revalidate=604800, stale-if-error=604800
  Link: </llms.txt>; rel="alternate"; type="text/markdown"
/interactive
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, stale-while-revalidate=86400, stale-if-error=604800
  Cloudflare-CDN-Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400, stale-while-revalidate=604800, stale-if-error=604800
/fast/
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, stale-while-revalidate=86400, stale-if-error=604800
  Cloudflare-CDN-Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400, stale-while-revalidate=604800, stale-if-error=604800

# editor.js is unhashed and only pulled on demand when the owner clicks Edit.
# Short browser TTL keeps edits current; longer edge TTL keeps it a HIT.
/editor.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, stale-while-revalidate=86400
  Cloudflare-CDN-Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400

# /assets holds both Vite content-hashed JS and NON-hashed images copied from
# public/assets. Because the filenames are not all content-hashed, keep a modest
# 1-hour browser TTL (not a year of immutable) so a replaced image is picked up,
# with a longer edge TTL + stale-while-revalidate to stay fast.
/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600, stale-while-revalidate=86400, stale-if-error=604800
  Cloudflare-CDN-Cache-Control: public, max-age=604800, stale-while-revalidate=604800, stale-if-error=604800
